# Xenoblade decompilation (auto)

> **Source of truth:** `.claude/skills/xenoblade-decomp/SKILL.md`. This rule is a
> mirror for Cursor; keep it in sync with the `.claude` copy.

At the **start of every task** in this repository:

1. Read `.cursor/skills/xenoblade-decomp/SKILL.md` and follow it.
2. Consult `PLAN.md` before changing gameplay, render, input, or memory behavior.
3. Use `tools/coop/run.py` for build/diff/cycle loops — do not improvise a separate pipeline.

**Policy:** all decompilation targets require **`EQUIVALENT_MATCH`** (function fuzzy ≥ 50% + SMT `EQUIVALENT` under effect-aware `auto` + split-size fit) or **`FULL_MATCH`** (100% static + split-size fit).

**MWCC knowledge:** before matching, search by exact function/symbol and observed mismatch with `python3 tools/mwcc_kb.py search ... --json`, then open relevant records with `show <id> --json`; **append reusable patterns and breakthroughs** to `docs/MWCC_REFERENCE.md` when found (not only in `attempts.jsonl`).

**Source language:** decompilation output is **high-level C/C++ only** — no `asm void` / whole-function asm bodies, `.s` units, register variables, or stack-offset tricks in `src/**` / `libs/**` (retail asm is reference-only; §17.6 allows single-instruction inline asm only).

When editing `src/**`, `libs/**`, or `configure.py`, run `coop run cycle` or `coop run diff` for the affected unit before claiming a target is complete.

**Split object size:** decomp `.text` must fit the retail split slice (`config/<region>/splits.txt`). Run `python3 tools/coop/run.py size <unit>` — `diff`, `cycle`, and `behaviour compare` also print a `size:` line and fail when over budget.

**Below the acceptance bar:** keep iterating toward `EQUIVALENT_MATCH` / `FULL_MATCH` (or §17.6 exceptions). `cycle` automatically probes equivalence once fuzzy ≥ 50%. Optional PPC harness via `behaviour ppc` when present. Host dual-oracle tests were removed.
